WEBVTT

00:08:28.731 --> 00:08:31.991
This kind of behavior was what led Jobs
to get forced out of Apple --

00:08:32.015 --> 00:08:34.015
his own company -- in the 80s.

00:08:34.547 --> 00:08:36.818
Take it from one
of his longtime collaborators,

00:08:36.842 --> 00:08:39.462
Apple engineer and designer, Jony Ive.

00:08:39.486 --> 00:08:42.400
He told Walter Isaacson
that when Jobs got frustrated,

00:08:42.424 --> 00:08:45.419
his way to achieve catharsis
was to hurt someone.

00:08:45.931 --> 00:08:47.097
According to Ive,

00:08:47.121 --> 00:08:50.026
Jobs felt he had a liberty
and a license to do that.

00:08:50.427 --> 00:08:52.434
WI: Working with him,

00:08:52.458 --> 00:08:56.166
you know, I was subject to watching him

00:08:56.190 --> 00:09:00.276
sort of, have that
very "mercurial" personality,